Barbadian singer, Rihanna has acquired a mansion in West Hollywood for $6.8 million days after Kendall Jenner moved out of the neighborhood.The songstress new home rivals even the most luxurious of celebrity homes. The newly refurbished 7,200 sq ft Old Hollywood estate boasts six bedrooms and ten bathrooms, and 18,000 sq ft of space in total. It also has an expansive master suite which features an en-suite lounge with custom Ebony wood vaulted ceilings, fireplace and floor-to-ceiling windows leading out to a private balcony.The singer reportedly got it for a bargain, having saved $1.2million off the $8million original asking price.Continue to see photos of the house. Loading...